<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n56103d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56103d">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56103d"> 103(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> perfect hill</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[THE CAUSE OF THE BATTLE OF CNUCHA]</font> <br>Almu&mdash;beautiful was the woman&mdash; <br>Wife of Nuada the Great, son of Achi; <br>She entreated&mdash;the division was just&mdash; <br>That her name should be on the <mark>perfect hill</mark>. A stronghold was built by the druid then in Almu, and <i>Alamu</i> (lime) was rubbed to its wall, until it was all white; and it was from that the name &ldquo;Almu&rdquo; was applied to it, of which was said: <small> Tom Peete Cross and Clark Harris Slover, <a name="AIT1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AIT1"><cite title="source">Ancient Irish Tales</cite></a>  ([Nov. 1936]) 357</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
